    <h1>üõ°Ô∏è Security Policy & Vulnerability Disclosure</h1>
    <p>At <strong>CMSForNerd</strong>, we take the security of our users seriously. If you believe you have found a security vulnerability, we encourage you to let us know right away.</p>

    <hr>

    <h3>1. Reporting a Vulnerability</h3>
    <p>Please do not use public GitHub issues for security reports. Instead, email your findings to <strong>security@cmsfornerd.test</strong>.</p>
    
    <ul>
        <li><strong>MUST:</strong> Include a detailed description of the vulnerability.</li>
        <li><strong>MUST:</strong> Provide steps to reproduce the issue (PoC).</li>
        <li><strong>SHOULD:</strong> Include potential impact and mitigation suggestions.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>2. Our Commitment</h3>
    <p>If you follow these guidelines, we promise to:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Acknowledge receipt of your report within <strong>72 hours</strong>.</li>
        <li>Provide an estimated timeframe for a fix.</li>
        <li>Notify you when the vulnerability is patched.</li>
        <li>Give credit in our <a href="hall-of-fame.php">Hall of Fame</a>.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>3. Prohibited Actions</h3>
    <p>To remain in "Good Faith" status, researchers <strong>MUST NOT</strong>:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Access or modify data that does not belong to them.</li>
        <li>Execute Denial of Service (DoS) attacks.</li>
        <li>Use social engineering or phishing against our users.</li>
    </ul>
</div>

